transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling by. This is Charles.

Speaker 2: I'll call you back in a minute, Ray.

Speaker 1: Hey, yes, sir. How you doing?

Speaker 2: I'm good. How about yourself?

Speaker 1: Yeah. I got two charges that shouldn't be on my thing.

Speaker 2: I only ordered one thing, and I got three charges.

Speaker 1: One of them is fine.

Speaker 2: My name is Anthony Welch.

Speaker 1: Gotcha. You're in Cleveland, Ohio?

Speaker 2: Yes. Yes.

Speaker 1: It looks like we filed the refund orders for all three charges yesterday and deactivated the account as well.

Speaker 2: Huh?

Speaker 1: We refunded everything yesterday, so it'll take a couple of days to hit your account.

Speaker 2: No, y'all was only supposed to refund two things, not three.

Speaker 1: Yeah, but it looks like we received disputes for everything, so we just refunded everything.

Speaker 2: So what do I do?

Speaker 1: You got to talk to your bank, because at this point, we've already deactivated your account because of the dispute,

Speaker 2: so you're no longer allowed to order with us anymore.

Speaker 1: Good job. But do you see where y'all order one thing, and y'all charge for three things, though?

Speaker 2: Yeah. Next time, you got to call in and figure that out with us and not talk to your bank,

Speaker 1: because you make us look really, really bad with the banks when you file a dispute like that.

Speaker 2: So at this point, brother, you're blacklisted from ever ordering from us again.

Speaker 1: So what do I do if I want to order something? That's what I'm saying.

Speaker 2: Y'all charge me for three things, and y'all's only supposed to charge me.

Speaker 1: You got to go to Bluetooth. You got to go to somewhere else, your doctor.

Speaker 2: I don't know, but you can't order with us anymore, unfortunately.

Speaker 1: Okay. No problem.

Speaker 2: All right, then. Hope you have a good one.
